Command reference

Command reference#

If you use arcos, you should already be pretty comfortable with a UNIX-like shell or the craftos shell.
But hereâ€™s a basic command reference
ls <directory>
Lists a directory
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # cd /
2    root@arcos / # ls
3    apis apps config data rom services startup.lua system temporary user
4    root@arcos / #
cd <directory>
Changes into directory. You can either use relative paths (ex. cd system) or absolute ones (ex. cd /system)
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # cd /
2    root@arcos / # cd system
3    root@arcos /system #
cp <source> <target>
Copies file <source> into <target>
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # ls
2    file.lua
3    root@arcos /user/root # cp file.lua file2.lua
4    root@arcos /user/root # ls
5    file.lua file2.lua
6    root@arcos /user/root #
mv <source> <target>
Moves <source> to <target>
Same as cp but deletes the old file
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # ls
2    file.lua
3    root@arcos /user/root # mv file.lua file2.lua
4    root@arcos /user/root # ls
5    file2.lua
6    root@arcos /user/root #
cat <file>
Reads <file> and outputs itâ€™s contents
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # ls
2    tip.txt
3    root@arcos /user/root # cat tip.txt
4    The arcos source code is available at https://www.github.com/mirkokral/ccarcos/.
5    root@arcos /user/root #
mkdir <folder>
Creates a folder
Example:
 1    root@arcos /user/root # ls
 2    tip.txt
 3    root@arcos /user/root # mkdir test
 4    root@arcos /user/root # ls
 5    test tip.txt
 6    root@arcos /user/root # mv tip.txt test/tip.txt
 7    root@arcos /user/root # ls
 8    test
 9    root@arcos /user/root # ls test
10    tip.txt
11    root@arcos /user/root #
rm <file/folder>
Removes a file or folder
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # ls
2    tip.txt
3    root@arcos /user/root # rm tip.txt
4    root@arcos /user/root # ls
5
6    root@arcos /user/root #
arc fetch
Fetches the latest repository information
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # arc fetch
2    root@arcos /user/root #
arc install <package>
Installs a package
Example:
 1    root@arcos /user/root # arc fetch
 2    root@arcos /user/root # arc install craft
 3    These packages will be installed:
 4
 5    rednet craft
 6
 7    Do you want to proceed? [y/n] y
 8    (1/2) rednet
 9    (2/2) craft
10    Done
11    root@arcos /user/root # craft
12    CraftOS 1.8 Compat on arcos 24.08 "Vertica" (Alpha release)
13    missingno
14    > hello
15    Hello, world!
16    >
arc uninstall <package>
Uninstalls a package
Example:
1    root@arcos /user/root # arc uninstall craft
2    These packages will be uninstalled:
3
4    craft
5
6    Do you want to proceed? [y/n] y
7    root@arcos /user/root # craft
8    [string "eval"]:1: '=' expected near <eof>
9    root@arcos /user/root #
